G-7b (the Quake gate, TAPESTRY.md section 9/18.9) -- musl-INTERNAL path
opens rerouted onto the patched open(). The stdio openers (fopen,
__fopen_rb_ca, tmpfile) call musl's sys_open MACRO -- the RAW
__syscall(SYS_open/SYS_openat, ...) -- which bypasses the 0009/0021
boundary-line openat() FUNCTION entirely and dies on the unwired 0xFFFF
sentinel (-ENOSYS). No prior pouch program ever fopen()ed by path
(stratumd uses open(); the hello probes use stdio on inherited fds), so
the gap sat latent until TyrQuake's COM_FileOpenRead -> fopen(pak0.pak)
silently found no pak ("Playing shareware version" + the palette
Sys_Error were both downstream of ZERO packfiles registering).

The fix routes the three call sites through the public open() -- the
patched function that resolves via SYS_open = 65 (stalk; real -errno).
Upstream musl deliberately uses the raw syscall there (no interposition,
no cancellation point); under pouch the patched function IS the syscall
boundary, so the reroute is the correct shape (fchmodat / posix_spawn /
__map_file / __libc_start_main keep their raw calls -- their arms are
fail-soft or out of the v1.0 pouch envelope).

SCOPE (audit F2): only the READ arm is functional at v1.0.
fopen(path,"rb") / __fopen_rb_ca (O_RDONLY) now reach SYS_open and work
-- the pak0.pak path the gate needs. But the downstream openat() (0021)
still refuses O_CREAT / O_TMPFILE with ENOTSUP, so fopen(path,"w"/"a")
(O_WRONLY|O_CREAT|O_TRUNC) and tmpfile() (O_RDWR|O_CREAT|O_EXCL) now
return NULL with an HONEST ENOTSUP instead of the old blanket -ENOSYS --
fail-CLOSED, no regression (create-mode fopen never worked in pouch).
Consequence: interactive TyrQuake's config.cfg / demo record do not
persist (fail-soft; the read-only +timedemo gate is unaffected).
Create-mode fopen/tmpfile wait on the SYS_WALK_CREATE openat wiring
(the v1.x openat-O_CREAT gap).

--- a/src/stdio/__fopen_rb_ca.c
+++ b/src/stdio/__fopen_rb_ca.c
@@ -6,7 +6,8 @@
 {
 	memset(f, 0, sizeof *f);
 
-	f->fd = sys_open(filename, O_RDONLY|O_CLOEXEC);
+	/* pouch: route through the patched open() -- see fopen.c. */
+	f->fd = open(filename, O_RDONLY|O_CLOEXEC);
 	if (f->fd < 0) return 0;
 	__syscall(SYS_fcntl, f->fd, F_SETFD, FD_CLOEXEC);
 
--- a/src/stdio/fopen.c
+++ b/src/stdio/fopen.c
@@ -18,7 +18,10 @@
 	/* Compute the flags to pass to open() */
 	flags = __fmodeflags(mode);
 
-	fd = sys_open(filename, flags, 0666);
+	/* pouch: sys_open is the RAW SYS_openat -- an unwired 0xFFFF sentinel
+	 * on Thylacine. Route through the public open(), the 0009/0021
+	 * boundary-line (SYS_open = 65 stalk resolution). */
+	fd = open(filename, flags, 0666);
 	if (fd < 0) return 0;
 	if (flags & O_CLOEXEC)
 		__syscall(SYS_fcntl, fd, F_SETFD, FD_CLOEXEC);
--- a/src/stdio/tmpfile.c
+++ b/src/stdio/tmpfile.c
@@ -13,7 +13,8 @@
 	int try;
 	for (try=0; try<MAXTRIES; try++) {
 		__randname(s+13);
-		fd = sys_open(s, O_RDWR|O_CREAT|O_EXCL, 0600);
+		/* pouch: route through the patched open() -- see fopen.c. */
+		fd = open(s, O_RDWR|O_CREAT|O_EXCL, 0600);
 		if (fd >= 0) {
 #ifdef SYS_unlink
